<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05174d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05174d">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05174d"> 174(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Candlemas <font color="green">[knife]</font> / blackhafted knife</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The bit of wax candle which her husband was the carry in the centre of his palm would be, no doubt, <mark>a candle blessed on Candlemas Day, and the black-hafted knife</mark> was the only mortal weapon feared by the fairies. <small> Alfred Perceval Graves, <a name="PIIP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#PIIP"><cite title="source">The Preternatural in Early Irish Poetry</cite></a>, (1912) 124</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
